t=\"0.5,0.5\" alt=\"sundown6.jpg\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"57b3b9a803b72344e27a3bfa\" data-type=\"image\"><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p><\/a><a class=\"\n                sqs-block-image-link\n\n              \" href=\"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/sundown6.jpg\"><\/a><a class=\"\n                sqs-block-image-link\n\n              \" href=\"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/sundown6.jpg\"><\/a><a class=\"\n                sqs-block-image-link\n\n              \" href=\"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/sundown6.jpg\"><\/a><a class=\"\n                sqs-block-image-link\n\n              \" href=\"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/sundown6.jpg\">          <\/a><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1471830020405_122837\">\nOn this Sunday, we randomly decided to take a trip to Enchanted Rock. Enchanted Rock is about an hour from where I live, but I&#8217;d never taken the time to visit. I&#8217;m so glad we did. I went with my really close friends and we had such a good time. I was hoping that we went earlier in the day so it would still be warm out. Of course we ended up leaving much later than we planned for. Thankfully, It turned out to be a great thing because we got the chance to watch the sunset from the top of this granite rock. I love watching the sunset just as much as anyone else, but my favorite part of the day is after the sun has set and it creates a pink &amp; blue sky that resembles cotton candy. I don&#8217;t think I&#8217;ll ever be able to get over that.<\/p>\n<p id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1471830020405_122840\">If you live in Texas and you&#8217;re looking for an adventure , check out Enchanted Rock!<\/p>\n<div class=\"\n          image-block-outer-wrapper\n          layout-caption-below\n          design-layout-inline\n\n        \" data-test=\"image-block-inline-outer-wrapper\"><\/p>\n<figure class=\"\n              sqs-block-image-figure\n              i